x4freetext: The HI-13 Tandem Accelerator in China
Institute of Atomic Energy
Four runs of measurement with gas-in
(sample-in and out) and gas-out (sample-in and out)
were performed for each angle during the experiment.
For each event, there are three parameters which are
PH, PSD and TOF. PH and PSD are used for the detection
threshold determination and n-gamma discrimination.
Deuterium gas target had following parameters:
Length 30 mm, diam. 10 mm, on gold backing 0.5 mm.
Three main detectors ST-451 (10.16 x 5.08 cm)
and one monitor NE213 (2.54 x 2.54 cm) were used.
The influence of breakup source neutrons from D(d,np)
reactions was eliminated by using the combination of
abnormal and normal fast neutron TOF spectrometers.
Monte-Carlo simulated TOF spectra of the complete
angular distribution were iteratively adjusted to
the measured TOF spectra. The simulation comprised
the neutron production in the gas target and the
scattering geometry between target, sample and
detectors.
The uncertainties due to the statistical
uncertainty, the neutron detection efficiency (ERR-1),
the scattering angle(0.3 degr.),
the normalization (ERR-2) and the correction for
multiple scattering(ERR-3) have been
taken into account, including their correlation.
The uncertainty due to neutron detection
efficiency,
The uncertainty due to normalization,
The uncertainty due to correction for
multiple scattering.
